Chongzhi</a>, established a method<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus#cite_note-15"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up><sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Calculus#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> that would later be called =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavalieri%27s_principle" title=3D"=
Cavalieri's principle">Cavalieri's principle</a> to find the volume of a <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sphere" title=3D"Sphere">sphere</a>.
</p>
